# 🔐 Day 5 - Password Generator

This project is a simple yet effective password generator written in Python, created as part of the **100 Days of Code** challenge.

The user can specify the number of letters, symbols, and numbers to include, and the program generates a randomized, secure password.

## 🚀 Features

- Customizable password length and character mix
- Randomized password creation
- Includes letters, digits, and symbols

## 🛠️ Built With

- Python 3
- `random` module

## 🧠 What I Practiced

- Working with lists and loops
- String manipulation
- Randomization using `random.choice()` and `random.shuffle()`

---

Part of the [100 Days of Code](https://github.com/Synel96/100-Days-Of-Code) journey.
